The Bottom Line
This project taught me something important about how companies fail and how people lose jobs:
Startups die fast. They run out of money and shut down completely. It's dramatic but usually small scale.
Giants bleed slowly. They survive, but thousands of people lose jobs along the way. The damage is quieter but much bigger.
If you want to know which industries are risky to work in right now? Look at Retail and Food. If you want to know where most of the job losses actually happened? Look at the companies with the most money.
________________________________________
A note on the data: All numbers come from publicly reported layoff announcements between 2020 and 2023. This represents real people losing real jobs, not just statistics. Behind every data point is someone's paycheck.
